<subSubSection id="8F82F223629229F972837671A8541C5E" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" type="comments">
<paragraph id="3EA36A29EFB085C4BA2130C4F94ADBE6" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6AC7BBFBD01E18AE51112D4417A68BBF" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName id="E2B896AA64A7DC912A85A561CA2E043D" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa columbiensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="columbiensis">
<emphasis id="A06C28A482699B1A49C38A89B2F64B74" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">Xylocopa columbiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName id="A9CFDD5B90C7C390514EAAA622E8F479" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. andica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="andica">
<emphasis id="DF9F4BF94A864900D917FFD3AF876679" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">X. andica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D0AA9E78035A94D24956FE5CF7D61970" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. nigrocincta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="nigrocincta">
<emphasis id="6CD07E70F7B179258F55C7D2C05009CB" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">X. nigrocincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="1558A9B899ED3768C3AB162072DC4626" family="Apidae" genus="X." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="X. suspecta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="suspecta">
<emphasis id="E423C0360F492305BABDBA46BEE7B77E" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">X. suspecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It can be separated from those species by the coloration and punctation of terga, as well as the coloration of terga and wings, as indicated in the diagnosis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BDE8878DFEAF2C58747D0E4A1A7F15D7" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName id="07320E0407DEEC32CEDA128B74384CF2" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa columbiensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="columbiensis">
<emphasis id="2495F35CE42B9A476746DCD85AADE344" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">Xylocopa columbiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from six specimens (three females and three males) and no holotype was designated. We examined these specimens, which are in the MNHN, and chose one of the females as the lectotype to stabilize the name. The label data for this specimen are as follows: Chiriqui [white label, handwritten] / Museum Paris, Coll. J. 
<normalizedToken id="8410FFB6986A0485FCDDF871561C4361" originalValue="Pérez">Perez</normalizedToken>
/ Lectotype [red label] / Lectotype 
<taxonomicName id="05283E6F510BCB15D7917C1019A56063" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylocopa columbiensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="columbiensis">
<emphasis id="E0CBEC4D58CC1D14107888463ECBA809" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="35">Xylocopa columbiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="E8EC0B998804FA1486ECED46F9C6EE98" originalValue="Peréz">Perez</normalizedToken>
des. M. Lucia &amp; V.H. Gonzalez.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
